      <tr><td>J&#464;</td><td><span class="chinese-char">己</span></td><td>Earth</td><td>Yin</td></tr>
      <tr><td>G&#275;ng</td><td><span class="chinese-char">庚</span></td><td>Metal</td><td>Yang</td></tr>
      <tr><td>X&#299;n</td><td><span class="chinese-char">辛</span></td><td>Metal</td><td>Yin</td></tr>
      <tr><td>R&#233;n</td><td><span class="chinese-char">壬</span></td><td>Water</td><td>Yang</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gu&#464;</td><td><span class="chinese-char">癸</span></td><td>Water</td><td>Yin</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>The 12 Earthly Branches correspond to the 12 zodiac animals: <span class="chinese-char">子</span> (Rat), <span class="chinese-char">丑</span> (Ox), <span class="chinese-char">寅</span> (Tiger), <span class="chinese-char">卯</span> (Rabbit), <span class="chinese-char">辰</span> (Dragon), <span class="chinese-char">巳</span> (Snake), <span class="chinese-char">午</span> (Horse), <span class="chinese-char">未</span> (Goat), <span class="chinese-char">申</span> (Monkey), <span class="chinese-char">酉</span> (Rooster), <span class="chinese-char">戌</span> (Dog), <span class="chinese-char">亥</span> (Pig). Yang stems pair only with yang branches, and yin stems pair only with yin branches, producing exactly 60 unique combinations.</p>
</section>

